Rating: 4
This recipe was great. I added angel hair pasta which I used as a bottom layer, then field greens instead of watercress for the middle layer, then the scallops on top and finished with the hoisin mixture for a dressing. It tasted exactly like one of my favorite dishes at a local vietnamese restaurant and made a light, satisfying meal.

